                            <comment id="14573274" author="gnelson" created="Wed, 12 Apr 2023 02:27:01 -0700"  >Reproduced in 17.0.6 as well (and updated the Affects Version accordingly).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Laptop monitor at 150% with external monitor at 100%.  Laptop is initially the primary monitor.  Change primary monitor to the external display and the system tray icon moves from the 150% monitor to the 100% monitor  and gets corrupted.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14572052" author="gnelson" created="Wed, 5 Apr 2023 10:19:28 -0700"  >We upgraded to use 17.0.5 to pick up that bug fix, and with that version confirmed that the display scale issue was addressed for us.   However perhaps we are using 17.0.5-oracle as I notice that this version includes the backport in it as well. &lt;br/&gt;
